description: Data was loaded from dbSNP, build 151, released on April 24, 2018. These human single nucleotide variations, microsatellites, and small-scale insertions and deletions were downloaded via a VCF file from the NCBI and uploaded into BigQuery using the Google Variant Transforms tool (v0.2.0). More details: see https://github.com/ncbi/dbsnp/tree/master/Build%20Announcements/151, ftp://ftp.ncbi.nih.gov/snp/organisms/human_9606_b151_GRCh37p13/VCF/All_20180423.vcf.gz and https://github.com/googlegenomics/gcp-variant-transforms

fields.description: Reference bases (hg19)
fields.name: reference_name

fields.description: Start position (0-based). Corresponds to the first base of the string of reference bases.
fields.name: start_position

fields.description: End position (0-based). Corresponds to the first base after the last base in the reference allele.
fields.name: end_position

fields.description: Reference bases (hg19)

Alternate base.

alternate_bases

fields.description: Variant names (e.g., refSNP IDs)
fields.name: names

fields.description: Phred-scaled quality score = (-10log10)x probability of incorrect base call. Higher values imply better quality.
fields.name: quality

fields.description: List of failed filters (if any), or PASS indicating the variant has passed all filters.
fields.name: filter

fields.description: One record for each call
Name of the call.
fields.name: name

fields.description: Genotype of the call. "-1" is used in cases where the genotype is not called.
fields.name: genotype

fields.name: phaseset
call

fields.description: Integer value. Chr position reported in dbSNP
fields.name: RSPOS

fields.description: True/false. Is mutation (journal citation, explicit fact): a low frequency variation that is cited in journal and other reputable sources
fields.name: MUT

fields.description: True/false. From 1000 Genome phase 3
fields.name: KGPhase3

fields.description: True/false. UTR location at 5 end is in an untranslated region (UTR). FxnCode = 55
fields.name: U5

fields.description: An ordered, comma delimited list of allele frequencies based on TOPMed, starting with the reference allele followed by alternate alleles as ordered in the ALT column. The TOPMed minor allele is the second largest value in the list.
fields.name: TOPMED

fields.description: Integer value. First dbSNP Build for RS
fields.name: dbSNPBuildID

fields.description: True/false. Whether has Assembly conflict. This is for weight 1 and 2 variant that maps to different chromosomes on different assemblies.
fields.name: CFL

fields.description: Pairs, each of gene symbol:gene id. The gene symbol and id are delimited by a colon (:) and each pair is delimited by a vertical bar (|)
fields.name: GENEINFO

fields.description: Variant Suspect Reason Codes (may be more than one value added together) 0 - unspecified, 1 - Paralog, 2 - byEST, 4 - oldAlign, 8 - Para_EST, 16 - 1kg_failed, 1024 - other
fields.name: SSR

fields.description: True/false. Has reference. A coding region variation where one allele in the set is identical to the reference sequence. FxnCode = 8
fields.name: REF

fields.description: True/false. Whether genotypes available. The variant has individual genotype (in SubInd table).
fields.name: GNO

fields.description: True/false. Whether marker is on high density genotyping kit (50K density or greater).The variant may have phenotype associations present in dbGaP.
fields.name: HD

fields.description: True/false. Whether in acceptor splice site FxnCode = 73
fields.name: ASS

fields.description: True/false. Submitted from a locus-specific database
fields.name: LSD

fields.description: True/false. Whether the variant is assembly specific. This is set if the variant only maps to one assembly
fields.name: ASP

fields.description: Integer value. Variant Allele Origin: 0 - unspecified, 1 - Germline, 2 - Somatic, 3 - Both
fields.name: SAO

fields.description: True/false. Has non-synonymous missense A coding region variation where one allele in the set changes protein peptide. FxnClass = 42
fields.name: NSM

fields.description: True/false. Has non-synonymous nonsense A coding region variation where one allele in the set changes to STOP codon (TER). FxnClass = 41
fields.name: NSN

fields.description: DbSNP ID (e.g., rs number) A reference SNP ID number, or rs ID, is an identification tag assigned by NCBI to a group (or cluster) of SNPs that map to an identical location. The rs ID number, or rs tag, is assigned after submission. The refSNP (rs) number is a unique identifier for SNP and does not infer position. An rs number may have one or more positions on a sequence (ie. SNP located in repeated region). See https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK44417/#Content.what_is_a_reference_snp_or__rs_i
fields.name: RS

fields.description: True/false. Whether >5% minor allele frequency in each and all populations
fields.name: G5A

fields.description: True/false. Is Validated.This bit is set if the variant has 2+ minor allele count based on frequency or genotype data.
fields.name: VLD

fields.description: True/false. Has non-synonymous frameshift A coding region variation where one allele in the set changes all downstream amino acids. FxnClass = 44
fields.name: NSF

fields.description: An ordered, comma delimited list of allele frequencies based on 1000Genomes, starting with the reference allele followed by alternate alleles as ordered in the ALT column. Where a 1000Genomes alternate allele is not in the dbSNPs alternate allele set, the allele is added to the ALT column. The minor allele is the second largest value in the list, and was previuosly reported in VCF as the GMAF. This is the GMAF reported on the RefSNP and EntrezSNP pages and VariationReporter.
fields.name: CAF

fields.description: True/false. From 1000 Genome phase 1 (incl. June Interim phase 1)
fields.name: KGPhase1

fields.description: Integer value. Is Withdrawn by submitter.If one member ss is withdrawn by submitter, then this bit is set.If all member ss are withdrawn, then the rs is deleted to SNPHistory
fields.name: WTD

fields.description: 0 or 1. Whether RS is a common SNP. A common SNP is one that has at least one 1000Genomes population with a minor allele of frequency >= 1% and for which 2 or more founders contribute to that minor allele frequency.
fields.name: COMMON

fields.description: True/false. Links exist to PubMed Central article
fields.name: PMC

fields.description: True/false. Variant is Precious (Clinical, Pubmed Cited)
fields.name: PM

fields.description: True/false. In gene region for 5 end FxnCode = 15
fields.name: R5

fields.description: Variation Class (possible values include SNV, DIV, MNV, 0)
fields.name: VC

fields.description: True/false. Provisional Third Party Annotation(TPA) (currently rs from PHARMGKB who will give phenotype data)
fields.name: TPA

fields.description: True /false. In gene region for 3 end FxnCode = 13
fields.name: R3

fields.description: True/false. Microattribution/third-party annotation (TPA:GWAS,PAGE)
fields.name: MTP

fields.description: True/false. Whether >5% minor allele frequency in 1+ populations
fields.name: G5

fields.description: True/false. Whether in donor splice-site FxnCode=75
fields.name: DSS

fields.description: Variation Property. Documentation is at ftp://ftp.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/snp/specs/dbSNP_BitField_latest.pdf
fields.name: VP

fields.description: Integer value. Weight, 00 - unmapped, 1 - weight 1, 2 - weight 2, 3 - weight 3 or more
fields.name: WGT

fields.description: True/false. RS (refSNP) orientation is reversed
fields.name: RV

fields.description: True/false. UTR location at 3 end is in an untranslated region (UTR). FxnCode = 53
fields.name: U3

fields.description: True/false. Has 3D structure - SNP3D table
fields.name: S3D

fields.description: True/false. Has other variant with exactly the same set of mapped positions on NCBI reference assembly.
fields.name: OTH

fields.description: True/false. Has OMIM/OMIA
fields.name: OM

fields.description: True/false. Whether is variation is interrogated in a clinical diagnostic assay
fields.name: CDA

fields.description: True/false Whether in Intron FxnCode = 6
fields.name: INT

fields.description: True/false. Has synonymous A coding region variation where one allele in the set does not change the encoded amino acid. FxnCode = 3
fields.name: SYN

fields.description: True/false. Contig allele not present in variant allele list. The reference sequence allele at the mapped position is not present in the variant allele list, adjusted for orientation.
fields.name: NOC

fields.description: True/false. Has SubmitterLinkOut - From SNP->SubSNP->Batch.link_out
fields.name: SLO

fields.description: True/false. Rs cluster has non-overlapping allele sets. True when rs set has more than 2 alleles from different submissions and these sets share no alleles in common.
fields.name: NOV
